### Implementation 1
This implementation uses a combination of exponential and trigonometric functions to calculate the priority. It subtracts each bin size from the item, takes the exponential of the result, and adds the sine of the item divided by each bin size.

```python
def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    return np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * item / bins)
```

### Implementation 2
This function calculates the priority by multiplying the item with the standard deviation of the bins and then adding the exponential of the item minus each bin.

```python
def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    return item * np.std(bins) + np.exp(item - bins)
```

