### Bin Packing Problem:
The bin packing problem is a classic optimization problem where you have a set of items and you want to pack them into the minimum number of bins of a fixed size. In this case, each bin has the same capacity. The goal is to assign the item to the bin which gives the best priority according to the heuristic function.

The priority function is used to determine which bin to place the item into. The function takes the item and the current bins as input and returns a priority score for each bin. The item is then placed into the bin with the highest priority score.

### Heuristic Function:
