### Implementation 1:
This function calculates the priority by combining the exponential decay of the item size relative to each bin and the standard deviation of the bins, adding a sine component based on the ratio of the item to each bin.

```python
import numpy as np

def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.std(bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))
```

